(18, 1, '2023-10-06 16:19:35', '2023-10-06 16:19:35', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a styling language used in web development to control the presentation and layout of HTML documents. It allows web designers and developers to define how web content should look and be displayed on various devices and screen sizes. With CSS, you can specify properties such as colors, fonts, spacing, positioning, and more to customize the visual appearance of web elements. CSS rules are applied to HTML elements, providing separation between content and design, making it easier to maintain and update the look and feel of a website or web application across multiple pages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Css', 'These are css tutorials', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'css', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:19:35', '2023-10-06 16:19:35', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=18', 0, 'post', '', 0),
