(21, 1, '2023-10-06 16:21:03', '2023-10-06 16:21:03', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bootstrap is a popular open-source front-end framework for web development. It provides a collection of pre-designed HTML, CSS, and JavaScript components and templates that help developers create responsive and visually appealing websites and web applications quickly and efficiently. Bootstrap\'s components include navigation bars, buttons, forms, modals, and more, making it easy to build modern and consistent user interfaces. It also offers a responsive grid system, which ensures that web content adapts seamlessly to various screen sizes and devices. Bootstrap simplifies the development process and helps maintain a cohesive design across different parts of a website or application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Bootstrap', 'These are bootstrap tutorials', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bootstrap', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:21:03', '2023-10-06 16:21:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=21', 0, 'post', '', 0),
