(27, 1, '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>jQuery is a lightweight and widely-used JavaScript library that simplifies web development by providing a collection of pre-written JavaScript code. It streamlines tasks such as DOM (Document Object Model) manipulation, event handling, and AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML) requests. jQuery makes it easier for developers to create interactive and responsive web applications, as it abstracts many of the complexities and browser compatibility issues that can arise in pure JavaScript. It\'s particularly known for its concise syntax and extensive ecosystem of plugins, which enhance its functionality and make it a valuable tool for front-end web development. While still used, it has become less essential in recent years due to advancements in native JavaScript and modern web development practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'JQuery', 'These are jquery tutorials\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jquery', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=27', 0, 'post', '', 0),
