(29, 1, '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>jQuery is a lightweight and widely-used JavaScript library that simplifies web development by providing a collection of pre-written JavaScript code. It streamlines tasks such as DOM (Document Object Model) manipulation, event handling, and AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML) requests. jQuery makes it easier for developers to create interactive and responsive web applications, as it abstracts many of the complexities and browser compatibility issues that can arise in pure JavaScript. It\'s particularly known for its concise syntax and extensive ecosystem of plugins, which enhance its functionality and make it a valuable tool for front-end web development. While still used, it has become less essential in recent years due to advancements in native JavaScript and modern web development practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'JQuery', 'These are jquery tutorials\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '27-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '2023-10-06 16:25:26', '', 27, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=29', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(30, 1, '2023-10-06 16:26:49', '2023-10-06 16:26:49', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>PHP (Hypertext Preprocessor) is a server-side scripting language commonly used for web development. It is embedded within HTML code and executed on the web server, allowing developers to create dynamic and interactive web pages. PHP is versatile and well-suited for tasks such as handling form data, interacting with databases, generating content on-the-fly, and more. It is often used in conjunction with databases like MySQL to build web applications and websites that can store and retrieve data. PHP\'s popularity is driven by its ease of use, wide availability on web servers, and a large community of developers who contribute to its extensive ecosystem of libraries and frameworks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'PHP', 'These are php tutorials', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'php', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:26:49', '2023-10-06 16:26:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=30', 0, 'post', '', 0),
