(33, 1, '2023-10-06 16:28:02', '2023-10-06 16:28:02', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Laravel is a popular open-source PHP web application framework known for its elegance and developer-friendly features. It simplifies the process of building robust and scalable web applications by providing a structured and expressive syntax. Laravel includes a wide range of built-in tools and libraries for common tasks like routing, authentication, database management, and more, reducing development time and promoting best practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some of Laravel\'s notable features include its powerful ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) called Eloquent, a templating engine called Blade, and a comprehensive ecosystem of extensions and packages known as \"Laravel packages\" that enhance its functionality. Additionally, Laravel emphasizes modern development practices such as dependency injection and test-driven development (TDD), making it a favorite choice for developers seeking to create high-quality web applications efficiently.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Laravel', 'These are laravel tutorials', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'laravel', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:28:02', '2023-10-06 16:28:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=33', 0, 'post', '', 0),
