(39, 1, '2023-10-06 16:30:40', '2023-10-06 16:30:40', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kotlin is a modern, statically-typed programming language developed by JetBrains. It is designed to be fully interoperable with Java and is often used for Android app development. Kotlin aims to improve upon some of Java\'s limitations by providing a more concise, expressive, and safer syntax.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Key features of Kotlin include null safety, which helps prevent null pointer exceptions, extension functions for adding new functionality to existing classes, and a concise syntax that reduces boilerplate code. Kotlin is fully supported by Google for Android app development, making it a popular choice for building Android applications. Additionally, it can be used for a wide range of other application types, including server-side development and desktop applications, making it a versatile language in the world of software development.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Kotlin', 'These are kotlin tutorials', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kotlin', '', '', '2023-10-06 16:30:40', '2023-10-06 16:30:40', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=39', 0, 'post', '', 0),
